issues.title: Per-Flow multipath
issues.body:
Hey,

commits.message:
Initialing handling of ARP packets, with the intention of eventually
removing dependence on buggy HostTracker.

Add init to CalculateDataRates to ensure maps are re-initialized on
startup.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jjbunn/MultipathODL

Conflicts:
	opendaylight/multipath/src/main/java/org/opendaylight/controller/multipath/MultiPath.java
Minor fixes.
Various fixes.

Mods to RoundRobinPathSelector, and some changes in the reactive flow
writing.
Enhancements and fixes. Install flows for Ping ICMP traffic.

Implementation of reactive mode Flow writing, fixes to Northbound for new
syntax in setupflows.

Mods to CalculateDataRates to better trap errors, and reduce polling
interval. Various tweaks to MultiPath.java.

Numerous modifications, additions and improvements. Notably data rate
calculator, flow installs, and new endpoints in Northbound.
Was missing these files from the previous commit!

New RESTful endpoints in Multipath.Northbound. New Data Rate Calculator
scheduled thread in Multipath. New code in available bandwidth path
calculator.
New endpoints in Multipath Northbound REST interface.
First commit, based on clone of ODL

Add exists method on DOMStoreReadTransaction and DOMDataReadTransaction

Introducing this API does not impact clients as it is mostly internal.

One reason for adding this API is because of ensureParentsByMerge used in a couple of places
which keeps checking if a parent node exists by reading a node to figure out if it exists. This is
fine for the InMemoryDataStore but it can be terrible in a distributed data store where the shard
which contains the data is remote. All sorts of overhead is associated with a remote read including
serialization which can actually be pretty expensive.

Configuration service uses an inconsistent hashcode in the clustered data structure

to propagation issues, because the clustering services implementation
